---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="About" animated={false}>
	<main
		class="flex justify-center flex-row flex-wrap w-screen px-10 lg:w-1/2 2xl:w-1/2 max-w-[760px] min-h-screen pt-48 animate-[0.75s_fade-in_ease-in-out]"
	>
		<div class="justif-center flex flex-col">
			<div class="py-5">
				<h1 class="text-gray-200 font-hype font-thin text-4xl md:text-6xl">
					Welcome to
				</h1>
				<h1
					class="text-gray-200 font-hype font-black text-4xl md:text-6xl"
				>
					mrxEE
				</h1>
			</div>
			<span class="text-gray-200 font-sans text-lg md:text-1xl py-3">
				mrxEE (MUREX Experimental Engineering) is MUREX Robotics's
				highly experimental research division. Calling upon our
				foundation of innovative, open-source electrical engineering
				(hence the origins of EE) designs, we push the absolute limits
				of modern day robotics. Beyond the MATE ROV Competition, our
				true goal is to change the world around us with groundbreaking
				innovation. The industry doesn't move us –– <b> we move it</b>.
				We achieve what no other team in the world is capable of. And we
				do it <b>incessantly</b>.
			</span>

			<span class="text-gray-200 font-sans text-lg md:text-1xl py-3">
                Email: <a href="mailto:murex@mrx.ee" class="font-hype font-black">murex@mrx.ee</a>
			</span>
			<span class="text-gray-200 font-hype text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black">
				ACHIEVEMENTS
			</span>
			<span class="text-gray-200 font-sans text-lg md:text-1xl py-3">
    <ol class="px-5 flex gap-3 flex-col">
        <li>
            <span class="text-gray-200 font-hype text-xl md:text-2xl font-black">Networking/Data</span>
            <ol class="pl-5">
                <li>- [Aug. 2024] World's smallest and lowest cost networking switch.
                    <ol class="pl-5">
                        <li>- #1 on HN with +600 upvotes</li>
                        <li>- Published on Tom's Hardware, All3DP, Techspot, r/Hardware, Interesting Engineering, and more.</li>
						<li>- Over 5 million views across YouTube, Instagram, and industry platforms/magazines
                    </ol>
                </li>
                <li>- [Dec. 2023] World's first open-source Ethernet Switch, MUREX Ethernet Switch</li>
                <li>- [Nov. 2023] World's first open demo of OFDM (orthogonal frequency division multiplexing) over galvanically isolated DC power lines, mrxPLC</li>
                <li>- [Jun. 2023] Custom one-to-many, duplex, high-speed, asynchronous communication protocol, MASCP</li>
            </ol>
        </li>
		<li>
            <span class="text-gray-200 font-hype text-xl md:text-2xl font-black">Power Electronics </span>
            <ol class="pl-5">
				<li>- [Dec. 2025] One of the highest data density (triple-channel power monitoring with an embedded controller) power modules, MUREX Smart Power Board </li>
				<li>- [Nov. 2024] Open-sourced design and demonstration of a 25A ideal-diode protection board for ROVs, mrxShield </li>
                <li>- [Oct. 2024] Thumb-sized 12A 5V DC-DC converter with 95% efficiency</li>
                <li>- [Dec. 2023] World's smallest open-source dual-output high power module designed for 12V/5V/3.3V DC applications, MUREX Power Board</li>
            </ol>
        </li>
        <li>
            <span class="text-gray-200 font-hype text-xl md:text-2xl font-black">Propulsion</span>
            <ol class="pl-5">
			    <li>- [Mar. 2025] Customized open-source BLHELI_S firmware configuration for a 4-1 ESC driving t200 thrusters</li>
				<li>- [Jan. 2025] World’s first open-source USB-modular and highest-power density sensorless field-oriented control ESC hardware design</li>
                <li>- [Nov. 2023] World's first modular serial single ESC, MUREX ANYESC</li>
            </ol>
        </li>
        <li>
            <span class="text-gray-200 font-hype text-xl md:text-2xl font-black">Software</span>
            <ol class="pl-5">
                <li>- [Mar. 2024] World's first open-source implementation of a USB3.0, MUREX Carrier Board controller</li>
                <li>- [Jan. 2024] World's first use of H.264 hardware encoding on the Allwinner H3 SoC using a mainline Linux kernel, unnamed</li>
                <li>- [Apr. 2024] Xbox trigger support for Ardupilot + QGroundControl, unnamed</li>
                <li>- [Dec. 2023] Custom Linux operating system, mrxOS</li>
                <li>- [Mar. 2024] World's first native arm64 macOS of QGroundControl, mrxGCS</li>
                <li>- [Dec. 2023] Custom Ardusub autopilot, mrx</li>
                <li>- [Dec. 2023] Novel, direct-compilation of the Linux Kernel with a virtualized Apple Silicon macOS environment and minimal overhead, unnamed</li>
            </ol>
        </li>
    </ol>
</span>
		</div>
	</main>
</Layout>
